The paper focuses on center-based clustering, which is a fundamental problem in data analysis and falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The use of the MapReduce computational model suggests that the paper also falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper presents approximation algorithms for clustering problems, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithms are based on coreset construction, which involves compressing the input data, and this technique is often used in information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper deals with metric spaces, which is a topic in mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
